AB  - World equilibria with trade in both goods and some factors are studied when international factor endowment differences are the cause of trade. A generalized Heckscher-Ohlin theorem is presented. The goods trade patterns with and without factor trade are compared. Factor trade and goods trade tend to be substitutes (complements) if traded and non-traded factors are cooperative (non-cooperative).
