T1  - Profitability of export restraint
AU  - Ono, Yoshiyasu
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 16
IS  - 3
SP  - 335
EP  - 343
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/05/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0022-1996(84)80010-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022199684800100
AB  - This paper analyzes the effect of quotas or voluntary export restraints upon each producer's profits in the case of an oligopoly with one foreign producer. In this oligopoly all producers, including the foreign producer, can get greater profits under some protective quotas than under no restraints. Furthermore, the optimal export restraint for the foreign producer with a low marginal cost is smaller than his optimal export under no restraints. Accordingly, export restraints may be sought by the foreign producer as a strategic behavior to increase profits.
ER  - 

