AB  - This paper comments on Brodsky (1984) in which he refers to my November 1981 article. The paper reiterates the point that the standard deviation cannot be used to draw statistical inferences when the underlying distribution is non-normal stable Paretian. In such a case, both the scale and characteristic exponent have to be considered.
